Chubb Says April, May Storms Cost Insurer Up to $310 Million

-- B y   B r o o k e   S u t h e r l a n d
-- 
2011-06-20T20:43:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-20/chubb-says-april-may-storms-cost-insurer-up-to-310-million.html
Chubb Corp. (CB)  the insurer of luxury
homes and corporate boards, said storms in April and May will
cost the company $250 million to $310 million before tax.  The natural disasters, including tornadoes, will cost 55
cents to 68 cents a share after tax in the second quarter, the
Warren, New Jersey-based insurer said today in a statement
distributed by PR Newswire.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brooke Sutherland in New York at 
 Bsutherland5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Kraut at   dkraut2@bloomberg.net  